<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-08-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-08-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="336" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d336">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/1490.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Santo Domingo</hi></placeName>, <lb/>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-25">
                                    <hi rend="italic">August 25, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Conference yesterday and today with Bordas and his Minister. Have
                            obtained full acceptance of President Wilson’s plan. Proclamation of
                            resignation by Bordas being prepared to be issued to Dominican people on
                            our order. Expect to settle on name of Provisional President tomorrow
                            and if possible induct him into office by Thursday at three o’clock.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Fort</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>